WEBVTT

00:21.260 --> 00:24.060
CHAPTER IV.

00:24.780 --> 00:32.540
I, therefore, the prisoner of the Lord, beseech you, that ye walk worthy of the vocation wherewith

00:32.540 --> 00:39.700
ye are called, with all lowliness and meekness, with long suffering, forbearing one another

00:39.700 --> 00:45.860
in love, endeavouring to keep the unity of the spirit in the bond of peace.

00:46.600 --> 00:53.700
There is one body, and one spirit, even as ye are called, in one hope of your calling,

00:54.280 --> 01:03.620
one Lord, one faith, one baptism, one God and Father of all, who is above all, and through all,

01:03.940 --> 01:10.760
and in you all. But unto every one of us is given grace according to the measure of the gift of

01:10.760 --> 01:21.040
Christ. Wherefore, he saith, when he ascended up on high, he led captivity captive, and gave gifts unto

01:21.040 --> 01:29.540
men. Now, that he ascended, what is it but that he also descended first into the lower parts of the

01:29.540 --> 01:38.560
earth? He that descended is the same also that ascended up far above all heavens, that he might

01:38.560 --> 01:48.180
fill all things. And he gave some apostles, and some prophets, and some evangelists, and some

01:48.180 --> 01:54.620
pastors and teachers, for the perfecting of the saints for the work of the ministry, for the

01:54.620 --> 02:02.100
edifying of the body of Christ, till we all come in the unity of the faith, and of the knowledge of

02:02.100 --> 02:10.620
the Son of God, unto a perfect man, unto the measure of the stature of the fullness of Christ,

02:11.040 --> 02:18.020
that we henceforth be no more children tossed to and fro, and carried about with every wind of

02:18.020 --> 02:25.460
doctrine, by the slight of men, and cunning craftiness, whereby they lie in wait to deceive.

02:25.460 --> 02:34.960
But speaking the truth in love, may grow up into him in all things, which is the head, even Christ,

02:35.840 --> 02:42.980
from whom the whole body fitly joined together and compacted by that which every joint supplyeth,

02:43.940 --> 02:50.600
according to the effectual working in the measure of every part, maketh increase of the body,

02:50.600 --> 02:57.480
unto the edifying of itself in love. This I say therefore, and testify in the Lord,

02:57.800 --> 03:06.340
that ye henceforth walk not as other Gentiles walk, in the vanity of their mind, having the

03:06.340 --> 03:13.560
understanding darkened, being alienated from the life of God through the ignorance that is in them,

03:13.560 --> 03:20.940
because of the blindness of their heart, who, being past feeling, have given themselves over

03:20.940 --> 03:29.000
to lasciviousness, to work all uncleanness with greediness, but ye have not so learned Christ.

03:29.740 --> 03:37.400
If so be that ye have heard him, and have been taught by him, as the truth is in Jesus,

03:37.400 --> 03:43.280
that ye put off concerning the former conversation, the old man, which is corrupt,

03:43.600 --> 03:51.280
according to the deceitful lusts, and be renewed in the spirit of your mind, and that ye put on

03:51.280 --> 03:58.580
the new man, which after God is created in righteousness and true holiness, wherefore putting

03:58.580 --> 04:06.420
away lying, speak every man truth with his neighbour, for we are members one of another.

04:07.420 --> 04:15.220
Be ye angry, and sin not, let not the sun go down upon your wrath, neither give place to the devil,

04:16.040 --> 04:22.700
let him that stole steal no more, but rather let him labour, working with his hands the thing which

04:22.700 --> 04:31.000
is good, that he may have to give to him that needeth. Let no corrupt communication proceed out

04:31.000 --> 04:38.660
of your mouth, but that which is good to the use of edifying, that it may minister grace unto the

04:38.660 --> 04:46.080
hearers, and grieve not the Holy Spirit of God, whereby ye are sealed unto the day of redemption.

04:46.840 --> 04:54.200
Let all bitterness and wrath and anger and clamour and evil speaking be put away from you,

04:54.200 --> 05:03.580
with all malice, and be ye kind one to another, tender-hearted, forgiving one another,

05:03.640 --> 05:06.740
even as God for Christ's sake hath forgiven you.

05:09.000 --> 05:18.540
Be ye therefore followers of God as dear children, and walk in love, as Christ also hath loved us,

05:18.540 --> 05:25.740
and hath given himself for us an offering and a sacrifice to God for a sweet smelling savour.

05:26.560 --> 05:34.360
But fornication and all uncleanness or covetousness, let it not be once named among you,

05:34.880 --> 05:42.840
as becometh saints, neither filthiness, nor foolish talking, nor jesting which are not convenient,

05:43.500 --> 05:52.020
but rather giving of thanks. For this ye know, that no whoremonger, nor unclean person, nor

05:52.020 --> 05:58.720
covetous man, who is an idolater, hath any inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and of God.

05:59.680 --> 06:06.100
Let no man deceive you with vain words, for because of these things cometh the wrath of God

06:06.100 --> 06:12.860
upon the children of disobedience. Be not ye therefore partakers with them, for ye were

06:12.860 --> 06:20.420
sometimes darkness, but now are ye light in the Lord. Walk as children of light, for the fruit

06:20.420 --> 06:27.700
of the Spirit is in all goodness and righteousness and truth, proving what is acceptable unto the

06:27.700 --> 06:35.680
Lord. And have no fellowship with the unfruitful works of darkness, but rather reprove them.

06:36.100 --> 06:41.680
For it is a shame even to speak of those things which are done of them in secret.

06:42.660 --> 06:49.260
But all things that are reproved are made manifest by the light, for whatsoever doth

06:49.260 --> 06:57.060
make manifest is light. Wherefore he saith, Awake thou that sleepest, and arise from the dead,

06:57.700 --> 07:04.400
and Christ shall give thee light. See then that ye walk circumspectly, not as fools,

07:04.400 --> 07:12.900
but as wise, redeeming the time, because the days are evil. Wherefore be ye not unwise,

07:13.280 --> 07:20.480
but understanding what the will of the Lord is. And be not drunk with wine wherein is excess,

07:21.120 --> 07:27.840
but be filled with the Spirit, speaking to yourselves in psalms and hymns and spiritual

07:27.840 --> 07:36.040
songs, singing and making melody in your heart to the Lord, giving thanks always for all things

07:36.040 --> 07:44.660
unto God, and the Father, in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, submitting yourselves one to another

07:44.660 --> 07:52.860
in the fear of God. Wives, submit yourselves unto your own husbands, as unto the Lord.

07:52.860 --> 07:58.700
For the husband is the head of the wife, even as Christ is the head of the church,

07:59.060 --> 08:06.400
and he is the saviour of the body. Therefore as the church is subject unto Christ, so let the

08:06.400 --> 08:13.920
wives be to their own husbands in every thing. Husbands, love your wives, even as Christ also

08:13.920 --> 08:20.940
loved the church and gave himself for it, that he might sanctify and cleanse it with the washing of

08:20.940 --> 08:28.100
water by the word, that he might present it to himself a glorious church, not having spot

08:28.100 --> 08:37.800
or wrinkle or any such thing, but that it should be holy and without blemish. So ought men to love

08:37.800 --> 08:44.860
their wives as their own bodies. He that loveth his wife loveth himself, for no man ever yet hated

08:44.860 --> 08:53.860
his own flesh, but nourisheth and cherisheth it, even as the Lord the church. For we are members

08:53.860 --> 09:02.000
of his body, of his flesh, and of his bones. For this cause shall a man leave his father and mother,

09:02.380 --> 09:09.420
and shall be joined unto his wife, and they too shall be one flesh. This is a great mystery,

09:09.420 --> 09:16.480
but I speak concerning Christ and the church. Nevertheless, let every one of you in particular

09:16.480 --> 09:23.480
so love his wife even as himself, and the wife see that she reverence her husband.

09:25.060 --> 09:32.760
CHAPTER VI Children, obey your parents in the Lord, for this is right. Honour thy father and mother,

09:32.760 --> 09:40.540
which is the first commandment with promise, that it may be well with thee, and thou mayest

09:40.540 --> 09:48.080
live long on the earth. And ye fathers, provoke not your children to wrath, but bring them up

09:48.080 --> 09:56.000
in the nurture and admonition of the Lord. Servants, be obedient to them that are your

09:56.000 --> 10:01.840
masters according to the flesh, with fear and trembling, and singleness of your heart,

10:01.840 --> 10:08.800
as unto Christ, not with eye-service, as men-pleasers, but as the servants of Christ,

10:09.220 --> 10:15.860
doing the will of God from the heart, with goodwill doing service, as to the Lord and not to men,

10:16.360 --> 10:21.580
knowing that whatsoever good thing any man doeth, the same shall he receive of the Lord,

10:21.800 --> 10:29.000
whether he be bond or free. And ye masters, do the same things unto them, forbearing threatening,

10:29.000 --> 10:35.100
knowing that your master also is in heaven, neither is there respect of persons with him.

10:35.520 --> 10:41.000
Finally, my brethren, be strong in the Lord, and in the power of his might.

10:41.960 --> 10:49.120
Put on the whole armour of God, that ye may be able to stand against the wiles of the devil.

10:49.660 --> 10:56.080
For we wrestle not against flesh and blood, but against principalities, against powers,

10:56.080 --> 11:03.120
against the rulers of the darkness of this world, against spiritual wickedness in high places.

11:04.240 --> 11:09.780
Wherefore, take unto you the whole armour of God, that ye may be able to withstand

11:10.320 --> 11:18.840
in the evil day, and having done all, to stand. Stand therefore, having your loins girt about

11:18.840 --> 11:25.100
with truth, and having on the breastplate of righteousness, and your feet shod with the

11:25.100 --> 11:32.160
preparation of the gospel of peace. Above all, taking the shield of faith, wherewith ye shall

11:32.160 --> 11:38.500
be able to quench all the fiery darts of the wicked. And take the helmet of salvation,

11:38.980 --> 11:44.660
and the sword of the spirit, which is the word of God. Praying always with all prayer,

11:45.040 --> 11:51.360
and supplication in the spirit, and watching thereunto with all perseverance, and supplication

11:51.360 --> 11:59.760
for all saints. And for me, that utterance may be given unto me, that I may open my mouth boldly,

12:00.680 --> 12:07.140
to make known the mystery of the gospel, for which I am an ambassador in bonds, that therein

12:07.140 --> 12:14.200
I may speak boldly, as I ought to speak. But that ye also may know my affairs, and how I do,

12:14.400 --> 12:20.560
Tychicus, a beloved brother and faithful minister in the Lord, shall make known to you all things,

12:20.560 --> 12:27.420
whom I have sent unto you for the same purpose, that ye might know our affairs,

12:27.820 --> 12:35.580
and that ye might comfort your hearts. Peace be to the brethren, and love with faith from God the

12:35.580 --> 12:44.660
Father, and the Lord Jesus Christ. Grace be with all them that love our Lord Jesus Christ in sincerity.

12:44.660 --> 12:46.380
Amen.

